The paper deals with selecting policies for large Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) using machine learning techniques. The paper discusses the use of decision lists and ensemble learning, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of PGraphplan, which is a planning algorithm used in the field of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the work to the relational reinforcement-learning problem, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and programming languages (cs.PL).
